      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "`InactivityCheck()` already logs a reason for any case where it returns true, eg:\r\n\r\n```\r\n2023-09-26T07:21:14.013289Z [net] socket receive timeout: 1201s peer=745   <==== this one\r\n2023-09-26T07:21:14.014945Z [net] disconnecting peer=745\r\n2023-09-26T07:21:14.016616Z [net] Cleared nodestate for peer=745\r\n\r\n2023-09-26T08:33:15.016157Z [net] version handshake timeout peer=9862    <=== and this one\r\n2023-09-26T08:33:15.016539Z [net] disconnecting peer=9862\r\n2023-09-26T08:33:15.017321Z [net] Cleared nodestate for peer=9862\r\n```\r\n\r\nDoes an extra log entry here actually help? Would adding the word \"disconnecting\" to the log entries in `InactivityCheck()` be better?",
